s they encounter a more thorough understanding the Daodejing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aTaoism. 0aTaoist philosophyvEarly works to 1800. 0aTaoist philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Taoist.2bisacsh1 aWu, Charles Q.1 aWu, Charles Q., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824857660423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780824857660/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles